-- Language: en_US
insert or replace into EnglishText
  (Tag,                                                                   Text)
values
  ("LOC_TECH_CALENDAR_HD_QUOTE_1",                                        "There was nothing brought together, nothing which could make a noise, nor anything which might move, or tremble, or could make noise in the sky. -- Popul Vuh"),
  ("LOC_TECH_CALENDAR_HD_QUOTE_2",                                        "In the first year of the Taichu era, the year was designated as 'Yanfeng Shetige' under the Jupiter chronological system, the month was named 'Bijju,' the day's celestial stem and earthly branch combination was Jiazi, and at midnight, the new moon coincided with the winter solstice.[NEWLINE] - Sima Qian, Shiji"),
  ("LOC_TECH_PAPER_MAKING_HD_QUOTE_1",                                    "The beauty of the paper is precious, the integrity of the formula, the purity of the body and the chastity of the nature. -- Fu Xian, Paper Fugue "),
  ("LOC_TECH_PAPER_MAKING_HD_QUOTE_2",                                    "The experienced man reads with two eyes, one seeing the words on the page and the other seeing the back of the paper. -- Goethe"),
  ("LOC_TECH_COMPASS_HD_QUOTE_1",                                         "A navigator knows geography; at night he watches the stars, at day he watches the sun, and at cloudy days he watches the compass. -- Pingzhou Ketan"),
  ("LOC_TECH_COMPASS_HD_QUOTE_2",                                         "Foreigners use compasses for navigation, but China uses them for feng shui. -- Lu Xun"),
  ("LOC_TECH_PHYSICS_HD_QUOTE_1",                                         "The most incomprehensible thing about the world is that it is comprehensible.-- Albert Einstein"),
  ("LOC_TECH_PHYSICS_HD_QUOTE_2",                                         "Give me a fulcrum and I can lift the whole earth. -- Archimedes"),
  ("LOC_TECH_BIOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                         "All life comes from life. -- Louis Pasteur"),
  ("LOC_TECH_BIOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                         "Nüwa has a body, who makes it? -- Qu Yuan, Heavenly Questions"),
  ("LOC_TECH_ALCHEMY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                         "Separabis terram ab igne, subtile ab spisso, suaviter, magno cum ingenio.[NEWLINE] - Tabula Smaragdina"),
  ("LOC_TECH_ALCHEMY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                         "Gold takes cinnabar as its root, blended with mercury, it transmutes. Transformation springs from its nature, end and beginning in mutual cause. To become an immortal through elixir, work with things of the same kind: plant rice using grains as seed, hatch chickens using their eggs.[NEWLINE] - Wei Boyang, Cantong Qi"),
  ("LOC_TECH_TEXTILE_HD_QUOTE_1",                                         "Young men who are my suitors, though royal Odysseus now is dead, [NEWLINE]Forbear to urge my marriage till I complete this robe,— its threads must not be wasted,—[NEWLINE]A shroud for lord Laeärtes, against the time when the sad doom of death that lays men low shall overtake him.[NEWLINE] - Homer, Odyssey"),
  ("LOC_TECH_TEXTILE_HD_QUOTE_2",                                         "Flowers fall rustling on my scarf and sleeves; From north to south of the village silk-worms weave. An old man sells cucumbers beneath an old tree.[NEWLINE] - Su Shi, Huanxisha"),
  ("LOC_TECH_FUEL_HD_QUOTE_1",                                            "Heaven and Earth form the cosmic forge,creation's hand the primal fire does urge;[NEWLINE]Yin and Yang burn as charcoal bright, all things smelted in bronze light.[NEWLINE] - Jia Yi, On the Owl"),
  ("LOC_TECH_FUEL_HD_QUOTE_2",                                            "In threadbare robe he shivers in the cold, yet fears his fuel won't sell—prays freeze takes hold.[NEWLINE] - Bai Juyi, The Old Charcoal Seller"),
  ("LOC_TECH_SADDLE_HD_QUOTE_1",                                          "mijin spent three nights within the forest and, saying, “I shall go out” at the moment when he was drawing nigh, leading his horse, his saddle loosed itself and remained behind.[NEWLINE] - The Secret History of the Mongols"),
  ("LOC_TECH_SADDLE_HD_QUOTE_2",                                          "To east market for a gallant steed he rides,[NEWLINE]To west for saddlecloth with leathern sides,[NEWLINE]To south for braided reins his way he takes,[NEWLINE]To north for stout whip that his hand shall shake.[NEWLINE] - Ballad of Mulan"),
  ("LOC_TECH_GEOMATICS_HD_QUOTE_1",                                       "The art of cartography rests on six principles profound: First, Fenlü—scale to map the spatial dimensions around;Second, Zhunwang—alignment to orient positions sound; Third, Daoli—routes to measure distances over ground; Fourth, Gaoxia—heights and depths; Fifth, Fangxie—slopes inclined; Sixth, Yuzhi—curves and straights combined— these three adapt to terrain, each custom-designed to reconcile all variations, harsh or kind.[NEWLINE] - Yu Gong, Preface of Yu Gong Map"),
  ("LOC_TECH_GEOMATICS_HD_QUOTE_2",                                       "Eratosthenes of Cyrene, employing mathematical theories and geometrical methods, discovered from the course of the sun the shadows cast by an equinoctial gnomon, and the inclination of the heaven that the circumference of the earth is two hundred and fifty-two thousand stadia, that is, thirty-one million five hundred thousand paces.[NEWLINE] - Vitruvius, De Architectura"),
  ("LOC_TECH_ARCH_HD_QUOTE_1",                                            "“Why do you speak to me of the stones? It is only the arch that matters to me.” Polo answers: “Without stones there is no arch.”[NEWLINE] - Italo Calvino, Invisible Cities"),
  ("LOC_TECH_ARCH_HD_QUOTE_2",                                            "Nine Fords and Nine Stars spanning the stream;[NEWLINE]When the world's in order, bridges cross free;[NEWLINE]The stone arch soars to meet the sky's eternity.[NEWLINE] - Li Ao, Ode to Zhaozhou Stone Bridge"),
  ("LOC_TECH_OCEANOGRAPHY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                    "The ocean's tribes of fish teem beyond measure, yet few are known to science, named, or deemed a treasure— a truth all naturalists should heed with care.[NEWLINE] - Jeong Yak-jeon, The Book of Fish"),
  ("LOC_TECH_OCEANOGRAPHY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                    "It is true that of the whole of nature the sea is most detrimental to the stomach in a multitude of ways, with its multitude of dishes and of appetizing kinds of fish to which the profits made by those who catch them spell danger.[NEWLINE] - Pliny the Elder, Natural History"),
  ("LOC_TECH_GEOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                         "While on imperial mission to Hebei, northward along the Taihang Mountains I rode: cliffs held embedded shells of clams and snails, and pebbles like bird's eggs—a stony load— stretched band-like across the rocks. This proved the land was ancient coastline, though now from eastern strand a thousand li lies distant.[NEWLINE] - Shen Kuo, Dream Pool Essays"),
  ("LOC_TECH_GEOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                         "The first phenomenon that presents itself to our attention is this: the ground beneath our feet is hollow, its vaulted structures stretching in near-unbroken continuity across vast regions—even continuing beneath the very floor of the sea.[NEWLINE] - Immanuel Kant, On the Causes of the Earth's Convulsions, Occasioned by the Calamity That Visited Upon the Western Lands of Europe Toward the Close of the Last Year"),
  ("LOC_TECH_REFRIGERATION_HD_QUOTE_1",                                   "Many years later as he faced the firing squad, Colonel Aureliano Buendía was to remember that distant afternoon when his father took him to discover ice.[NEWLINE] - Gabriel Garcia Marquez, One Hundred Years of Solitude"),
  ("LOC_TECH_REFRIGERATION_HD_QUOTE_2",                                   "A thousand bamboos—forests of emerald hue;Lotus blooms—scattered points of crimson glow.[NEWLINE]By waterside pavilion, cooled through and through, On jade mat chilled, no sleeper lies below.[NEWLINE]An amber cup, like wine that drips unseen, A crystal screen, breeze-kissed and gleaming bright.[NEWLINE] - Liu Yuxi, Summer Retreat at the Imperial Son-in-Law's Waterside Pavilion"),
  ("LOC_TECH_MEDICAL_SCIENCE_HD_QUOTE_1",                                 "Take a handful of sweet wormwood, steep in two liters of water— wring out the juice, consume in full.[NEWLINE] - Ge Hong, Emergency Formulae at an Elbow's Length"),
  ("LOC_TECH_MEDICAL_SCIENCE_HD_QUOTE_2",                                 "More than that, a medicament may be hotter towards the body of Peter than it is to the body of Paul. It is important to know this when choosing medicines with the object of altering the temperament."),
  ("LOC_TECH_MODERN_AGRICULTURE_HD_QUOTE_1",                              "A single grain of rice can sustain a nation, yet may also bring a nation down.[NEWLINE] - Yuan Longping, Interviewed by CCTV"),
  ("LOC_TECH_MODERN_AGRICULTURE_HD_QUOTE_2",                              "A nation whose thriving agricultural economy can furnish all conditions for prosperity, where cultivation yields no less than 100% net surplus—its tillers must not neglect the knowledge essential to their art.[NEWLINE] - François Quesnay, Writed for Victor de Riqueti, marquis de Mirabeau, Philosophie rurale"),
  ("LOC_TECH_MODERN_TRAFFIC_HD_QUOTE_1",                                  "When Heaven and Earth commune, the myriad beings find free flow; When high and low commune, their purposes become one.[NEWLINE] - Commentary on the Appended Judgments, Tai Hexagram, I Ching"),
  ("LOC_TECH_MODERN_TRAFFIC_HD_QUOTE_2",                                  "On weekends his Rolls-Royce became an omnlibus, bearing parties to and from the city between nine in the morning and long past midnight, whjle his station wagon Scampered like a brlsk yellow bug to meet all trains.[NEWLINE] - F. Scott Fitzgerald, The Great Gatsby"),
  ("LOC_TECH_CATERPILLAR_TRACK_HD_QUOTE_1",                               "They built ten-thousand-hu barges to ferry them across, and broad-rimmed carts with four wheels— their tracks four feet wide, dug two feet deep— hauled the load to Ye.[NEWLINE] - Book of Jin, Records of Shi Jilong"),
  ("LOC_TECH_CATERPILLAR_TRACK_HD_QUOTE_2",                               "General, your tank is a powerful vehicle[NEWLINE]It smashes down forests and crushes a hundred men.[NEWLINE]But it has one defect:[NEWLINE]It needs a driver.[NEWLINE] - Bertolt Brecht, General, your tank is a powerful vehicle"),
  ("LOC_TECH_GENETIC_ENGINEERING_HD_QUOTE_1",                             "You can stop splitting the atom; you can stop visiting the moon; you can stop using aerosols; you may even decide not to kill entire populations by the use of a few bombs. But you cannot recall a new form of life.[NEWLINE] - Erwin Chargaff, Letter to the editor of Science"),
  ("LOC_TECH_GENETIC_ENGINEERING_HD_QUOTE_2",                             "Did you read over the company's brochure and the spec sheets? The Nexus-6 brain unit they're using now is capable of selecting within a field of two trillion constituents, or ten million separate neural pathways.[NEWLINE] - Philip K. Dick, Do Androids Dream of Electric Sheep?"),
  ("LOC_TECH_INDUSTRIAL_AUTOMATION_HD_QUOTE_1",                           "The goal of the future is full unemployment, so we can play.[NEWLINE] - Arthur C. Clarke, interview with Los Angeles Free Press"),
  ("LOC_TECH_INDUSTRIAL_AUTOMATION_HD_QUOTE_2",                           "if, in like manner, the shuttle would weave and the plectrum touch the lyre without a hand to guide them, chief workmen would not want servants, nor masters slaves.[NEWLINE] - Aristotle, Politics"),
  ("LOC_TECH_INTERNET_HD_QUOTE_1",                                        "The Internet is the first thing that humanity has built that humanity doesn't understand, the largest experiment in anarchy that we have ever had.[NEWLINE] - Eric Schmidt"),
  ("LOC_TECH_INTERNET_HD_QUOTE_2",                                        "A bit has no color, size, or weight, and it can travel at the speed of light.[NEWLINE] - Nicholas Negroponte, Being Digital"),
  ("LOC_TECH_INTEGRATED_CIRCUIT_HD_QUOTE_1",                              "The complexity for minimum component costs has increased at a rate of roughly a factor of two per year. Certainly over the short term this rate can be expected to continue, if not to increase.[NEWLINE] - Gordon E. Moore, Cramming More Components onto Integrated Circuits"),
  ("LOC_TECH_INTEGRATED_CIRCUIT_HD_QUOTE_2",                              "All that had been done in the mid-twentieth century on “calculating machines” had been upset by Robertson and his positronic brain-paths. The miles of relays and photocells had given way to the spongy globe of plantinumiridium about the size of a human brain.[NEWLINE] - Issac Asimov, I, Robot"),
  ("LOC_TECH_VIRTUAL_REALITY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                 "My fascination with VR technology and multimedia lies in its power to vastly expand the human brain's perceptual faculties. Thus it propels humanity into unprecedented cognitive territories—a new historical epoch dawns![NEWLINE] - Qian Xuesen, Letter to Wang Chengewei"),
  ("LOC_TECH_VIRTUAL_REALITY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                 "Under bright ghosts burning through a blue haze of cigarette smoke, holograms of Wizard’s Castle, Tank War Europa, the New York skyline...[NEWLINE] - "),
  ("LOC_TECH_BIG_DATA_HD_QUOTE_1",                                        "They can use the system to go back in time and scrutinize every decision you've ever made, every friend you've ever discussed something with, and attack you on that basis to sort of derive suspicion from an innocent life and paint anyone in the context of a wrongdoer.[NEWLINE] - Edward Snowden, Interviewed by The Guardian"),
  ("LOC_TECH_BIG_DATA_HD_QUOTE_2",                                        "In 2007, for the first time ever, more information was generated in one year than had been produced in the entire previous five thousand years - the period since the invention of writing.[NEWLINE] - Jaap Bloem, Menno van Doorn, Sander Duivestein, Me the media: rise of the conversation society"),
  ("LOC_TECH_NAVIGATIONAL_INSTRU_HD_QUOTE_1",                             "And you, quadrant! What can you do but tell where the hand that holds you happens to be on this wide world? No more than that?Curse you![NEWLINE] - Herman Melville, Moby Dick"),
  ("LOC_TECH_NAVIGATIONAL_INSTRU_HD_QUOTE_2",                             "The Instruments necessarie for a skilfull Seaman are a Sea Compasse, a Crosse staffe, a Quadrant, an Astrolobe, a Chart, an instrument magnetical, for the finding of the variation of the Compasse, an Horizontal plaine Sphere, a Globe, and a paradoxall Compasse.[NEWLINE] - John Davis, The Seamans Secrets"),
  ("LOC_TECH_MODERN_COMMU_EQUIP_HD_QUOTE_1",                              "When wireless is perfectly applied, the whole earth will be converted into a huge brain, which in fact it is, all things being particles of a real and rhythmic whole. We shall be able to communicate with one another instantly, irrespective of distance.[NEWLINE] - Nikola Tesla, Interviewed by Collier's Magazine (1926)"),
  ("LOC_TECH_MODERN_COMMU_EQUIP_HD_QUOTE_2",                              "The development of international communications has brought the peoples of the world into close neighborhood. It is our hope that these means of communication will serve increasingly as a carrier of the message of peace for which we both work and pray.[NEWLINE] - Dwight D. Eisenhower. Exchange of Messages Between the President and Her Majesty Queen Elizabeth II on the 100th Anniversary of the Trans-Atlantic Cable"),
  
  ("LOC_CIVIC_SUPPLY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                         "A horse! A horse! My kingdom for a horse! -- Shakespeare, Richard III"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_SUPPLY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                         "As the old saying goes, before the armies move, food and fodder go first, and when the army is well fed, the battle is invincible. -- The Storys of the Qin King of the Great Tang Dynasty"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_ARCHAEOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                    "This is the reason for this study, which is intended to be used by the doctors and counsellors, and to make the world aware of the usefulness of the relics of Yin to scholars of history and scripture. --Wang Guowei, A Study of the First Kings and First Gentlemen as Found in the Divination of Yin"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_ARCHAEOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                    "The French Empire has appropriated half its treasures, and now it has the impudence to go to such lengths as to bring out for public exhibition, as owner, these beautiful ancient relics from the Yuanmingyuan. --Victor Hugo"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_LITERARY_TRADITION_HD_QUOTE_1",                             "The essay is a great and immortal event. --Cao Pi,  A Treatise on the Canon"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_LITERARY_TRADITION_HD_QUOTE_2",                             "I think tendencies should flow naturally from the sections and episodes, and not be specifically pointed out. --Frederic Engels"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_IMPERIAL_EXAMINATION_SYSTEM_HD_QUOTE_1",                    "The spring breeze is so fast that you can see all the flowers in Chang'an in one day. --Meng Jiao,  After the Examination"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_IMPERIAL_EXAMINATION_SYSTEM_HD_QUOTE_2",                    "It is all but impossible to conceive of a better government than that in which only those who have passed a rigorous examination are admitted to the government offices. -- Voltaire"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_EVOLUTION_THEORY_HD_QUOTE_1",                               "Ah, how magical! How many wonderful characters here; how beautiful are the human beings! O wondrous new world, to have such wonderful people! -- William Shakespeare, The Tempest"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_EVOLUTION_THEORY_HD_QUOTE_2",                               "We don't want change. Every change endangers stability. --Aldous Huxley, Brave New World"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_HISTORICAL_PHILOSOPHY_HD_QUOTE_1",                          "The book is called a factual record because it is good at ordering things, discriminating without being flashy, qualitative without being slang, straight in its text, and checkable in its matter, without false beauty or hidden evil. -- Ban Gu, The Book of Han"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_HISTORICAL_PHILOSOPHY_HD_QUOTE_2",                          "The only lesson that history teaches is that one never learns anything in history. --Georg Hegel, The Philosophy of History"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_ETHICS_HD_QUOTE_1",                                         "What gentleman was there when Adam and Eve laboured! --Florian Geyer"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_ETHICS_HD_QUOTE_2",                                         "The kind of career that requires people to work non-stop and becomes an integral part of their lives. In fact, it is the only possible motivation. -- Max Weber, The Protestant Ethic and the Spirit of Capitalism"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_SOCIAL_SCIENCE_HD_QUOTE_1",                                 "A science can only reach the point of true perfection when it applies mathematics successfully. -- Karl Marx"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_SOCIAL_SCIENCE_HD_QUOTE_2",                                 "Only society can make a general assessment of the value of life, and the individual can do nothing about it ...... -- Émile Durkheim, On Suicide"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_EARLY_WARFARE_HD_QUOTE_1",                                  "The most vital affairs of a state lie in sacrifices and warfare. Sacrifices involve distributing sacrificial meat (zhifan), and warfare requires receiving consecrated meat (shoushen). These are sacred rituals of utmost significance in matters pertaining to the divine.[NEWLINE] - Zuo Zhuan, The 13th Year of Duke Cheng of Lu"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_EARLY_WARFARE_HD_QUOTE_2",                                  "The mighty king hastened on and came to the bank of the Ulāya River. The two kings came together, engaging in battle. Fire flared up between them. The face of the sun was darkened by the dust (they raised up). Dust storms whirled; the storm whipped around.[NEWLINE] - Nebuchadnezzar I 11 Inscription"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_FUNERAL_HD_QUOTE_1",                                        "Who's buried with Duke Mu? The eldest of the three. [NEWLINE]This eldest worthy son Could be rivaled by none. [NEWLINE]Coming to the graveside, Who'd not be terrified? [NEWLINE]O good Heavens on high, Why shouid the worthy die?[NEWLINE] - Classic of Poetry, Airs of Qin, Buriat of Three Worthies"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_FUNERAL_HD_QUOTE_2",                                        "O, let not the pains of death which come upon thee enter into my body. [NEWLINE]I am the god Tem, and I am the foremost part of the sky, and the power which protecteth me is that which is with all the gods forever.[NEWLINE] - The Book of the Dead, translated by Sir Ernest Alfred Wallis Budge"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_HOUSEHOLD_REGISTRATION_HD_QUOTE_1",                         "When a wise and sagacious ruler governs the realm, they divide the capital into three administrative districts and the countryside into five regions, stabilize the dwellings of the people, ensure that all citizens are settled in their respective occupations.[NEWLINE] - Discourses of the States, Discourses of Qi"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_HOUSEHOLD_REGISTRATION_HD_QUOTE_2",                         "The people in Sung, WeI, Han and Liang adhere to the fundamental and till the soil. Among the common people and yeomanr every house prospers and every person is satisfied.[NEWLINE] - Huan Kuan, Discourses on Salt and Iron, Circulation of Goods"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_HERALDRY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                       "Heraldry has been contemptuously termed 'the science of fools with long memories.'[NEWLINE] - James Planche, The Pursuivant of Arms; Or, Heraldry Founded Upon Facts"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_HERALDRY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                       "The kirimon is a fundamental emblem of a stabilizing house. After Lord Hachiman's subjugation of Sadato, when proceeding to the capital, it was requested by the imperial court and this paulownia crest was bestowed upon him.[NEWLINE] - Records of Various Kamons"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_COMMERCIAL_CAPITALISM_HD_QUOTE_1",                          "This thought casts a terrible light upon our present epoch, in which, far more than at any former period, money sways the laws and politics and morals.[NEWLINE] - Honoré de Balzac, Eugénie Grandet"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_COMMERCIAL_CAPITALISM_HD_QUOTE_2",                          "Under a system of perfectly free commerce, each country naturally devotes its capital and labour to such employments as are most beneficial to each. This pursuit of individual advantage is admirably connected with the universal good of the whole.[NEWLINE] - David Ricardo, The Principles of Political Economy and Taxation"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_LAW_HD_QUOTE_1",                                            "Dura lex, sed led.[NEWLINE] - Latin proverb"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_LAW_HD_QUOTE_2",                                            "Laws in their most general signification, are the necessary relations resulting from the nature of things.[NEWLINE] - Montesquieu, The Spirit of Laws"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_JOURNALISM_STUDIES_HD_QUOTE_1",                             "Next came the “Gazette”, with this:[NEWLINE]WANTED TO KNOW. -- Will the new candidate for Governor deign to explain to certain of his fellow-citizens (who are suffering to vote for him!) the little circumstance of his cabin-mates in Montana losing small valuables from time to time, until at last, these things having been invariably found on Mr. Twain's person or in his “trunk”.[NEWLINE] - Mark Twain, Running for Governor"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_JOURNALISM_STUDIES_HD_QUOTE_2",                             "When rulers read these publications, they gain insights to assist governance; When intellectuals read them, they learn to recognize changes and adapt flexibly;When merchants and farmers read them, they access supply-demand information to facilitate trade activities.[NEWLINE] - Hong Rengan, A New Treatise on Aids to Administration"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_HUMAN_RIGHTS_HD_QUOTE_1",                                   "Man is born free; and everywhere he is in chains.[NEWLINE] - Jean-Jacques Rousseau, The Social Contract"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_HUMAN_RIGHTS_HD_QUOTE_2",                                   "Property being a sacred and inviolable right, no one can be deprived of it, unless a legally established public necessity evidently demands it, under the condition of a just and prior indemnity.[NEWLINE] - Declaration of the Rights of Man and of the Citizen"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_POLICE_SYSTEM_HD_QUOTE_1",                                  "There was of course no way of knowing whether you were being watched at any given moment. How often, or on what system, the Thought Police plugged in on any individual wire was guesswork.[NEWLINE] - George Owell, 1984"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_POLICE_SYSTEM_HD_QUOTE_2",                                  "Therefore, for any nation that seeks to govern well and maintain social order, it must begin with the police.[NEWLINE] - Huang Zunxian, Records of Japan"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_MUSEOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                      "“Museums are on the front lines of the fight for culture, of good with evil – in any case, of the fight against platitudes and primitiveness.”[NEWLINE]– Mikhail Piotrovsky, Director of the State Hermitage"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_MUSEOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                      "Every genuine work of art has as much reason for being as the earth and the sun.[NEWLINE] - Ralph Waldo Emerson"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_SOCIAL_SECURITY_SYSTEM_HD_QUOTE_1",                         "The end of government is to make the governed and the governors happy. That government then is thebest, which in practice produces the greatest happiness to the greatest number; including those who govern, and those who obey.[NEWLINE] - Robert Owen, The Principles of the Former Essays Applied to Government"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_SOCIAL_SECURITY_SYSTEM_HD_QUOTE_2",                         "If you're in trouble or hurt or need—go to poor people. They're the only ones that'll help—the only ones.[NEWLINE] - John Ernst Steinbeck, The Grapes of Wrath"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_PALEOBIOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                   "But there was a higher and subtler chemistry of Nature, which, working with great forces over long epochs, might well produce results which were impossible for us.[NEWLINE] - Arthur Konan Doyle, The Lost World"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_PALEOBIOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                   "I look at the geological record as a history of the world imperfectly kept, and written in a changing dialect.[NEWLINE] - Charles Darwin, The Origin of Species"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_ANTHROPOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                   "Democracy in government, brotherhood in society, equality in rights and privileges, and universal education, foreshadow the next higher plane of society to which experience, intelligence and knowledge are steadily tending. It will be a revival, in a higher form, of the liberty, equality and fraternity of the ancient gentes.[NEWLINE] - Lewis Henry Morgan, Ancient Society"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_ANTHROPOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                   "Thus the first and basic ideal of ethnographic field-work is to give a clear and firm outline of the social constitution, and disentangle the laws and regularities of all cultural phenomena from the irrelevances.[NEWLINE] - Bronisław Malinowski, Argonauts of the Western Pacific"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_URBAN_DESIGN_HD_QUOTE_1",                                   "The ultimate goal of all visual artistic activity is construction![NEWLINE] - Walter Gropius, Manifesto"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_URBAN_DESIGN_HD_QUOTE_2",                                   "Cities have the capability of providing something for everybody, only because, and only when, they are created by everybody.[NEWLINE] - Jane Jacobs, The Death and Life of Great American Cities"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_LEAGUE_OF_NATIONS_HD_QUOTE_1",                              "Any war or threat of war, whether immediately affecting any of the Members of the League or not, is hereby declared a matter of concern to the whole League, and the League shall take any action that may be deemed wise and effectual to safeguard the peace of nations.[NEWLINE] - Covenant of the League of Nations"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_LEAGUE_OF_NATIONS_HD_QUOTE_2",                              "Wilson, that intellectual, preached “justice” and “humanity” to those robbers day after day—organizing the “League of Nations”, hoping for “permanent peace”. It was truly like playing the lute to a cow. All he got were fierce glares from those robbers, while he himself grew sick with anger over them, leaving those who had faith in him utterly disheartened.[NEWLINE] - Li Dazhao, Secret Diplomacy and the Robber World"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_FINANCE_HD_QUOTE_1",                                        "Yesterday, all the newspapers splashed the news of the Central Army's victory. At the opening bell of the stock exchange's morning session, every bond shot up by two or three yuan. The market floor was packed with surging crowds of people; their shouts were like a battle charge on the front lines – no distinct words could be heard, nothing but a sea of upturned palms thrusting upwards.[NEWLINE] - Mao Dun, Midnight"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_FINANCE_HD_QUOTE_2",                                        "The world of finance is a mysterious world in which, incredible as the fact may appear, evaporation precedes liquidation.[NEWLINE] - Joseph Conrad, Victory: An Island Tale"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_HIGHER_EDUCATION_HD_QUOTE_1",                               "Were we not able to console ourselves with the Prophet and hisCompanions, and the scholars of religious learning and guidance,It would have been right for tears to flow from the eyes one afteranother, for the disappearance of teachers, and the extinctionof fires of learning.[NEWLINE] - Sidi Yahyā al-Tadallisi, Cited in Abd al-Rahman al-Sa'di, Tarikh al-Sudan"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_HIGHER_EDUCATION_HD_QUOTE_2",                               "The wind of freedom blows.[NEWLINE] - Motto of Stanford University"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_NEOCOLONIALISM_HD_QUOTE_1",                                 "The division of labor among nations is that some specialize in winning and others in losing.[NEWLINE] - Eduardo Galeano, Open Veins of Latin America"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_NEOCOLONIALISM_HD_QUOTE_2",                                 "A state can be said to be a neo-colonialist or client state if it is independent de jure and dependent de facto. It is a state where political power lies in the conservative forces of the former colony and where economic power remains under the control of international finance capital.[NEWLINE] - Kwame Nkrumah, Sham Independence"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_MODERNISM_HD_QUOTE_1",                                      "Things fall apart; [NEWLINE]the centre cannot hold.[NEWLINE] - William Butler Yeats, The Second Coming"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_MODERNISM_HD_QUOTE_2",                                      "And finally from a human view point we can see that theatre action is as beneficial as the plague, impelling us to see ourselves as wc are, making the masks fall and divulging our world’s lies, aimlessness, meanness, and even two-facedness. [NEWLINE] - Antoine Artaud, The Theatre and the Plague"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_INTERNATIONALISM_HD_QUOTE_1",                               "Desirous that all African States should henceforth unite so that the welfare and wellbeing of their peoples can be assured, [NEWLINE]Resolved to reinforce the links between our states by establishing and strengthening common institutions, [NEWLINE]Have agreed to the present Charter.[NEWLINE] - Charter of the Organization of African Unity"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_INTERNATIONALISM_HD_QUOTE_2",                               "The era when Western aggressors could occupy a country by merely setting up a few guns along an Eastern coast is gone forever. Any imperialist aggression today can be defeated by relying on the strength of the people.[NEWLINE] - Peng Dehuai, Report on the Work of the Chinese People's Volunteers in the War to Resist U.S. Aggression and Aid Korea"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_MODERN_MATIONAL_DEFENSE_HD_QUOTE_1",                        "I believe that I interpret the will of the Congress and of the people when I assert that we will not only defend ourselves to the uttermost but will make it very certain that this form of treachery shall never again endanger us.[NEWLINE] - Franklin Delano Roosevelt, Pearl Harbor speech"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_MODERN_MATIONAL_DEFENSE_HD_QUOTE_2",                        "He fell in October, 1918, on a day that was so quiet and still on the whole front, that the army report confined itself to the single sentence: All quiet on the Western Front.[NEWLINE] - Erich Maria Remarque, All quiet on the Western Front"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_MACRO_ECONOMICS_HD_QUOTE_1",                                "The ideas of economists and political philosophers, both when they are right or when they are wrong, are more powerful than is commonly understood. Indeed the world is ruled by little else.[NEWLINE] - John Maynard Keynes, The General Theory of Employment, Interest and Money"),
  ("LOC_CIVIC_MACRO_ECONOMICS_HD_QUOTE_2",                                "Capitalism is a bane compared with socialism. Capitalism is a boon compared with medievalism, small production, and the evils of bureaucracy which spring from the dispersal of the small producers.[NEWLINE] - Vladimir Lenin, Tax In Kind, Freedom To Trade And Concessions");

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Language: zh_Hans_CN
insert or replace into LocalizedText
  (Language,      Tag,                                                                    Text)
values
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_CALENDAR_HD_QUOTE_1",                                         "此处记述了如何：一切处于悬止，一切平静，处于静默；一切静止，寂静，而天穹的领域是空洞的。[NEWLINE]——《波波武经》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_CALENDAR_HD_QUOTE_2",                                         "太初元年，岁名“焉逢摄提格”，月名“毕聚”，日得甲子，夜半朔旦冬至。[NEWLINE]——司马迁《史记》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_PAPER_MAKING_HD_QUOTE_1",                                     "夫其为物，厥美可珍，廉方有则，体洁性贞。[NEWLINE]——傅咸《纸赋》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_PAPER_MAKING_HD_QUOTE_2",                                     "经验丰富的人读书用两只眼睛，一只眼睛看到纸面上的话，另一眼睛看到纸的背面。[NEWLINE]——约翰·沃尔夫冈·冯·歌德"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_COMPASS_HD_QUOTE_1",                                          "舟师识地理，夜则观星，昼则观日，阴晦观指南针。[NEWLINE]——《萍洲可谈》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_COMPASS_HD_QUOTE_2",                                          "外国用罗盘针航海，中国却用它看风水。[NEWLINE]——鲁迅"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_PHYSICS_HD_QUOTE_1",                                          "这个世界最不可理解的就是它竟然是可以理解的。[NEWLINE]——阿尔伯特·爱因斯坦"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_PHYSICS_HD_QUOTE_2",                                          "给我一个支点，我可以翘起整个地球[NEWLINE]——阿基米德"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_BIOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                          "所有生命都来自生命[NEWLINE]——路易斯·巴斯德"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_BIOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                          "女娲有体，孰制匠之？[NEWLINE]——屈原《天问》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_ALCHEMY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                          "伴随着崇敬与智慧，你应愉快地从烈火中分离泥土，从粗鄙中分离精细。[NEWLINE]——《翠玉录》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_ALCHEMY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                          "金以砂为主，秉和于水银。变化由其真，终始自相因。欲作伏食仙，宜以同类者，植禾当以谷，覆鸡用其卵。[NEWLINE]——魏伯阳《周易参同契》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_TEXTILE_HD_QUOTE_1",                                          "我的年轻的求婚人，英雄奥德修斯既已死，[NEWLINE]你们要求我再嫁，且不妨把婚期稍延迟，[NEWLINE]待我织完这匹布，免得我前工尽废弃，[NEWLINE]这是给英雄拉埃尔特斯织造做寿衣。[NEWLINE]——荷马《奥德赛》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_TEXTILE_HD_QUOTE_2",                                          "簌簌衣巾落枣花，村南村北响缫车， 牛衣古柳卖黄瓜。[NEWLINE]——苏轼《浣溪沙》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_FUEL_HD_QUOTE_1",                                             "天地为炉兮，造化为工；[NEWLINE]阴阳为碳兮，万物为铜。[NEWLINE]——贾谊《鵩鸟赋》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_FUEL_HD_QUOTE_2",                                             "可怜身上衣正单，心忧炭贱愿天寒。[NEWLINE]——白居易《卖炭翁》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_SADDLE_HD_QUOTE_1",                                           "帖木真在密林里住了三夜 ，想要出去，牵着马正走着，他的马鞍子脱落下来。他回头一看，见板胸仍旧扣着，肚带仍旧束着，而马鞍却脱落了。[NEWLINE]——《蒙古秘史》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_SADDLE_HD_QUOTE_2",                                           "东市买骏马，[NEWLINE]西市买鞍鞯，[NEWLINE]南市买辔头，[NEWLINE]北市买长鞭。[NEWLINE]——《木兰辞》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_GEOMATICS_HD_QUOTE_1",                                        "制图之体有六焉。一曰分率，所以辨广轮之度也。二曰准望，所以正彼此之体也。三曰道里，所以定所由之数也。四曰高下，五曰方邪，六曰迂直，此三者各因地而制宜，所以校夷险之异也。[NEWLINE]——裴秀《禹贡地域图序》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_GEOMATICS_HD_QUOTE_2",                                        "昔兰尼的埃拉托色尼运用数学理论和几何方法，根据太阳运行轨迹、春分晷针投射的阴影和天体的倾角，发现地球的周长是二十五万二千斯塔迪亚，也就是三千一百五十万步。[NEWLINE]——维特鲁威《论建筑》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_ARCH_HD_QUOTE_1",                                             "忽必烈汗默默地沉思了一阵，然后又问：“你为什么总跟我讲石头？对我来说只有桥拱最重要。”马可·波罗回答：“没有石头，就不会有桥拱了。”[NEWLINE]——伊塔洛·卡尔维诺《看不见的城市》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_ARCH_HD_QUOTE_2",                                             "九津九星横河中，[NEWLINE]天下有道津梁通，[NEWLINE]石穹隆兮与天终。[NEWLINE]——李翱《赵州石桥铭》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_OCEANOGRAPHY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                     "海中鱼族极繁，而传名者鲜，博物者所宜察也。[NEWLINE]——丁若铨《兹山鱼谱》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_OCEANOGRAPHY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                     "须知他们的道德败坏与奢侈之风，其滋生的最大源头莫过于贝类。诚然，在自然的全部产物中，海洋以无数方式对胃最为有害[NEWLINE]——它用大量诱人鱼类制作的菜肴造成伤害。[NEWLINE]——老普林尼《自然史》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_GEOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                          "予奉使河北，遵太行而北，山崖之间往往衔螺蚌壳及石子如鸟卵者，横亘石壁如带。此乃昔之海滨，今东距海已近千里。所谓大陆者，皆浊泥所湮耳。[NEWLINE]——沈括《梦溪笔谈》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_GEOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                          "引起我们注意的第一点就是，我们栖身于其上的土地是空心的，它的圆拱几乎连贯地通过一些辽阔的地带，甚至延伸到了最低的海底。[NEWLINE]——伊曼努尔·康德《就去年年底波及西欧各国的那场灾难论地震的原因》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_REFRIGERATION_HD_QUOTE_1",                                    "多年以后，面对行刑队，奥雷里亚诺·布恩迪亚上校将会回想起父亲带他去见识冰块的那个遥远的下午。[NEWLINE]——加夫列尔·加西亚·马尔克斯《百年孤独》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_REFRIGERATION_HD_QUOTE_2",                                    "千竿竹翠数莲红，水阁虚凉玉簟空。[NEWLINE]琥珀盏红疑漏酒，水晶帘莹更通风。[NEWLINE]——刘禹锡《刘驸马水亭避暑》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_MEDICAL_SCIENCE_HD_QUOTE_1",                                  "青蒿一握，以水二升渍，绞取汁，尽服之。[NEWLINE]——葛洪《肘后备急方》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_MEDICAL_SCIENCE_HD_QUOTE_2",                                  "同样一种药物可能在不同人身上所产生的热力效果不一样。当我们要选择药物来改变人体的配属时，了解这一点非常重要。[NEWLINE]——伊本·西纳《医典》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_MODERN_AGRICULTURE_HD_QUOTE_1",                               "一粒粮食能够救一个国家，也可以绊倒一个国家。[NEWLINE]——袁隆平，接受中国中央电视台采访"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_MODERN_AGRICULTURE_HD_QUOTE_2",                               "一个国家，如果它的富裕农业经济能保证提供繁荣的一切条件，如果农业能够提供不低于100%的纯产品，耕作者就不应忽视他们所需要的知识。[NEWLINE]——弗朗索瓦·奎奈，为老米拉波《农业哲学》所作"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_MODERN_TRAFFIC_HD_QUOTE_1",                                   "天地交而万物通也，上下交而其志同也。[NEWLINE]——《易传·彖传上·泰》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_MODERN_TRAFFIC_HD_QUOTE_2",                                   "每逢周末，他的劳斯莱斯轿车变成了公交车，从早上九点到午夜过后仍忙碌往返市区载送人群，他的旅行车则像只敏捷的黄色小虫，一蹦一跳地与每一班火车会合。[NEWLINE]——弗朗西斯·斯科特·菲茨杰拉德《了不起的盖茨比》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_CATERPILLAR_TRACK_HD_QUOTE_1",                                "造万斛舟以渡之，以四轮缠辋车，辙广四尺，深二尺，运至邺。[NEWLINE]——《晋书·石季龙载记》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_CATERPILLAR_TRACK_HD_QUOTE_2",                                "将军，你的坦克很强大，[NEWLINE]它能摧毁森林，粉碎一百个人。[NEWLINE]但它有一个缺陷：[NEWLINE]它需要一个驾驶员。[NEWLINE]——贝托尔特·布莱希特《将军，你的坦克很强大》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_GENETIC_ENGINEERING_HD_QUOTE_1",                              "你可以停止分裂原子；你可以停止登月；你可以停止使用气溶胶；你甚至可能决定不再用几枚炸弹来屠杀全体民众。但你无法召回一种新的生命形式。[NEWLINE]——埃尔文·查戈夫《致〈科学〉杂志编辑的信》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_GENETIC_ENGINEERING_HD_QUOTE_2",                              "“肯定是罗森公司新出的那些超级聪明的新型仿生人。”马斯滕小姐继续说，“看没看过他们公司的手册和说明书？他们现在所用的枢纽6型脑单元，已经能在两万亿个组分，或一千万个不同的神经通路间作选择。”[NEWLINE]——菲利普·迪克《仿生人能梦见电子羊吗？》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_INDUSTRIAL_AUTOMATION_HD_QUOTE_1",                            "未来的目标是让所有人失业，这样我们就可以好好玩。[NEWLINE]——亚瑟·C·克拉克，接受洛杉矶自由出版社采访"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_INDUSTRIAL_AUTOMATION_HD_QUOTE_2",                            "如果梭子能自己编织，如果琴拨能自己触动琴弦，都不需要人的双手，那么工匠也不再需要仆人，主人也不再需要奴隶。[NEWLINE]——亚里士多德《政治学》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_INTERNET_HD_QUOTE_1",                                         "互联网是首个为人类所创造，却不为人类所理解之物，也是有史以来我们在无政府状态下所进行的最疯狂尝试。[NEWLINE]——埃里克·施密特"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_INTERNET_HD_QUOTE_2",                                         "比特没有颜色、尺寸或重量，能以光速传播。它就好比人体内的DNA一样，是信息的最小单位。[NEWLINE]——尼古拉斯·尼葛洛庞帝《数字化生存》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_INTEGRATED_CIRCUIT_HD_QUOTE_1",                               "最低成本的电子元件对应的复杂度正以每年约翻一番的速度增长。短期内这一速度无疑将持续，甚至可能加快。[NEWLINE]——戈登·E·摩尔《在集成电路上容纳更多元件》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_INTEGRATED_CIRCUIT_HD_QUOTE_2",                               "二十世纪中叶在“计算机”上所做的一切发展，当时已被罗伯森与他的正子脑径路淘汰。绵延数里的继电器与光电管，让位给了铂铱合金的海绵状球体，后者的体积差不多与人脑相当。[NEWLINE]——艾萨克·阿西莫夫《我，机器人》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_VIRTUAL_REALITY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                  "我对灵境技术及多媒体的兴趣在于他能大大扩展人脑的知觉，因而它使人进入前所未有的新天地，新的历史时代要开始了！[NEWLINE]——钱学森《致汪成为的信》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_VIRTUAL_REALITY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                  "香烟的蓝色烟雾笼罩着那些明亮的全息影像：巫师城堡、欧罗巴坦克战、纽约的天际线……[NEWLINE]——威廉·吉布森《神经漫游者》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_BIG_DATA_HD_QUOTE_1",                                         "他们能够利用监控系统让时间倒流、明察秋毫，他们可以查出每一个你曾做过的决定，每一个和你说过话的朋友，在此基础之上制造出对你的怀疑，从而攻击你，将你描绘成一个罪犯，无论你的人生多么清白。[NEWLINE]——爱德华·斯诺登，接受《卫报》采访"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_BIG_DATA_HD_QUOTE_2",                                         "2007年，人类历史上首次出现这样的情况：一年内产生的信息量超过了自文字发明以来五千年间创造的所有信息的总和。[NEWLINE]——雅普·布洛姆、门诺·范多恩、桑德·杜伊维斯特恩《我即媒体：对话社会的崛起》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_NAVIGATIONAL_INSTRU_HD_QUOTE_1",                              "你啊，天文象限仪！你有什么本事呢？只不过在说明，把你握在手里的人，是在这广阔的世界的某一个角落。再也没有别的用处了！[NEWLINE]——赫尔曼·梅尔维尔《白鲸记》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_NAVIGATIONAL_INSTRU_HD_QUOTE_2",                              "熟练水手所需的仪器包括：航海罗经、十字测天仪、象限仪、星盘、海图、磁力仪（用于测定罗盘磁偏角）、水平平面球仪、地球仪以及特殊罗盘。[NEWLINE]——约翰·戴维斯《水手的秘密》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_MODERN_COMMU_EQUIP_HD_QUOTE_1",                               "当无线技术完美应用之时，整个地球将转化成一个巨大的大脑——事实上它本就是如此，万物皆是真实而有节奏的整体中的粒子。我们将能够无视距离，即刻与他人交流。[NEWLINE]——尼古拉·特斯拉，1926年接受《科利尔》杂志采访"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_TECH_MODERN_COMMU_EQUIP_HD_QUOTE_2",                               "国际通讯的发展使世界各国人民紧密相连。我们希望，这些通讯手段能够日益成为我们共同努力和祈祷的和平信息的载体。[NEWLINE]——德怀特·艾森豪威尔《总统与伊丽莎白二世女王在大西洋电缆百年纪念之际的通信》"),
  
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_SUPPLY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                          "一匹马！一匹马！我用王国换一匹马！[NEWLINE]——莎士比亚《理查三世》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_SUPPLY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                          "自古道三军未动，粮草先行，兵精粮足，战无不胜。[NEWLINE]——《大唐秦王词话》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_ARCHAEOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                     "由是有商一代，先公先王之名不见于卜辞者殆鲜。乃为此考，以质诸博士及参事,并使世人知殷虚遗物之有裨于经史二学者有如斯也。[NEWLINE]——王国维《殷卜辞中所见先公先王考》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_ARCHAEOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                     "法兰西帝国侵吞了一半宝物，现在，它居然无耻到这样的地步，还以所有者的身份把圆明园的这些美轮美奂的古代文物拿出来公开展览。[NEWLINE]——维克多·雨果"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_LITERARY_TRADITION_HD_QUOTE_1",                              "盖文章经国之大业，不朽之盛事。[NEWLINE]——曹丕《典论》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_LITERARY_TRADITION_HD_QUOTE_2",                              "我认为倾向应当从断面和情节中自然而然地流露出来,而不应当特地把它指点出来。[NEWLINE]——弗雷德里克·恩格斯"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_IMPERIAL_EXAMINATION_SYSTEM_HD_QUOTE_1",                     "春风得意马蹄疾，一日看尽长安花。[NEWLINE]——孟郊《登科后》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_IMPERIAL_EXAMINATION_SYSTEM_HD_QUOTE_2",                     "通过层层严格考试的人才能进入衙门任职，人们全然不可能设想一个比这更好的政府。[NEWLINE]——伏尔泰"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_EVOLUTION_THEORY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                "啊，多么神奇！这里有多少美妙的人物；人类多么美丽！奇妙的新世界啊，竟有这样美好的人！[NEWLINE]——威廉·莎士比亚《暴风雨》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_EVOLUTION_THEORY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                "我们不要变化。每一个变化都会危及安定。 [NEWLINE]——阿道司·赫胥黎《美丽新世界》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_HISTORICAL_PHILOSOPHY_HD_QUOTE_1",                           "服其善序事理，辨而不华，质而不俚，其文直，其事核，不虚美，不隐恶，故谓之实录。[NEWLINE]——班固《汉书》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_HISTORICAL_PHILOSOPHY_HD_QUOTE_2",                           "历史给人的唯一教训，就是人们从未在历史中吸取过任何教训。[NEWLINE]——格奥尔格·黑格尔《历史哲学》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_ETHICS_HD_QUOTE_1",                                          "亚当夏娃劳作之时，哪有什么绅士！[NEWLINE]——弗洛里安·盖耶"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_ETHICS_HD_QUOTE_2",                                          "这种需要人们不停地工作的事业，成为他们生活中不可或缺的组成部分。事实上，这是唯一可能的动机。[NEWLINE]——马克斯·韦伯《新教伦理与资本主义精神》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_SOCIAL_SCIENCE_HD_QUOTE_1",                                  "一门科学，只有当它成功地运用数学时，才能达到真正完善的地步。[NEWLINE]——卡尔·马克思"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_SOCIAL_SCIENCE_HD_QUOTE_2",                                  "只有社会才能对人生的价值做出总的评价，而个人对此是无能为力的……[NEWLINE]——埃米尔·涂尔干《自杀论》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_EARLY_WARFARE_HD_QUOTE_1",                                   "国之大事，在祀与戎，祀有执膰，戎有受脤，神之大节也。[NEWLINE]——《左传·成公十三年》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_EARLY_WARFARE_HD_QUOTE_2",                                   "强大的王向乌莱河畔疾驰，两位王者正面交锋刀兵相向。烈火在他们之间熊熊燃起，飞沙在战车上空遮天蔽日。沙尘肆虐四方，狂风席卷天地。[NEWLINE]——那布葛留崔一世第11号铭文"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_FUNERAL_HD_QUOTE_1",                                         "谁从穆公？子车奄息。[NEWLINE]维此奄息，百夫之特。[NEWLINE]临其穴，惴惴其栗。[NEWLINE]彼苍者天，歼我良人！[NEWLINE]——《诗经·秦风·黄鸟》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_FUNERAL_HD_QUOTE_2",                                         "哦，别让你所受的死亡痛苦进入我的身体。[NEWLINE]我是创世神泰姆，我处在天界的最高层，神力护佑着我和所有其他神灵直到永远。[NEWLINE]——欧内斯特·阿尔弗雷德·沃利斯·巴吉爵士译文《死者之书》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_HOUSEHOLD_REGISTRATION_HD_QUOTE_1",                          "圣王之治天下也，参其国而伍其鄙，定民之居，成民之事，陵为之终，而慎用其六柄焉。[NEWLINE]——《国语·齐语》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_HOUSEHOLD_REGISTRATION_HD_QUOTE_2",                          "宋、卫、韩、梁 ，好本稼穑，编户齐民，无不家衍人给。[NEWLINE]—— 桓宽 《盐铁论·通有》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_HERALDRY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                        "纹章学曾经长期被蔑称为“有好记性的傻瓜的科学”。[NEWLINE]——詹姆斯·普兰切《纹章传令官；或者说纹章学之事实》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_HERALDRY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                        "桐者，根本安家之纹也。八幡殿贞任御退治以后，御上洛之时，依被望申，下赐此桐纹。[NEWLINE]——《见闻诸家纹》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_COMMERCIAL_CAPITALISM_HD_QUOTE_1",                           "金钱控制法律，控制政治，控制风俗，到了前所未有的程度。[NEWLINE]——巴尔扎克《欧也妮·葛朗台》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_COMMERCIAL_CAPITALISM_HD_QUOTE_2",                           "在商业完全自由的制度下，各国都必然把它的资本和劳动用在最有利于本国的用途上。这种个体利益的追求很好地和整体的普遍幸福结合在一起。[NEWLINE]——大卫·李嘉图《政治经济学及赋税原理》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_LAW_HD_QUOTE_1",                                             "纵然峻法，亦为律法。[NEWLINE]——拉丁文谚语"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_LAW_HD_QUOTE_2",                                             "最广义的法，是指源于物之本质的必然联系。从这种意义上而言，万物皆有法：神有其法，物质世界有其法，超人智能有其法，兽有其法，人有其法。[NEWLINE]——孟德斯鸠《论法的精神》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_JOURNALISM_STUDIES_HD_QUOTE_1",                              "接着，《新闻报》刊登了这样一段话：“需要查证——马克·吐温先生在蒙大拿住宿的时候，经常小偷小摸，同宿旅伴常常丢失东西，而往往能在他的背包中找到它们。”天哪，我根本就没有去过蒙大拿州！[NEWLINE]——马克·吐温《竞选州长》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_JOURNALISM_STUDIES_HD_QUOTE_2",                              "设新闻馆以收民心公议，及各省郡县货价低昂，事势常变。 上览之，得以资治术；士览之，得以识变通；商农览之，得以通有无。[NEWLINE]——洪仁玕《资政新篇》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_HUMAN_RIGHTS_HD_QUOTE_1",                                    "人是生而自由的，但却无往不在枷锁之中。[NEWLINE]——让-雅克·卢梭《社会契约论》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_HUMAN_RIGHTS_HD_QUOTE_2",                                    "财产是不可侵犯与神圣的权利，除非合法认定的公共需要对它明白地提出要求，同时基于公正和预先补偿的条件，任何人的财产皆不可受到剥夺。[NEWLINE]——《人权宣言》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_POLICE_SYSTEM_HD_QUOTE_1",                                   "你无从知晓自己是否被监视，也无从猜测思想警察会以何种手段，在何时接通你前方的电屏。他们可能无时无刻不在监视着每一个人。[NEWLINE]——乔治·奥威尔《1984》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_POLICE_SYSTEM_HD_QUOTE_2",                                   "然则有国家者，欲治国安人，其必自警察始矣。[NEWLINE]——黄遵宪《日本国志》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_MUSEOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                       "博物馆处于文化斗争的前沿，扬善抑恶——总之，一直在同陈腐和原始的东西做斗争。[NEWLINE]——冬宫博物馆馆长米哈伊尔"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_MUSEOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                       "每一件伟大的艺术品都应如日月般长存。[NEWLINE]——拉尔夫·瓦尔多·爱默生《入世与离群》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_SOCIAL_SECURITY_SYSTEM_HD_QUOTE_1",                          "政府的目的是使被统治者和统治者都获得幸福。因此，最佳政府就是在实践中能为最大多数人——包括治理者与被治理者——创造最大幸福的政体。[NEWLINE]——罗伯特·欧文《论文四·将前论应用于治理之原则》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_SOCIAL_SECURITY_SYSTEM_HD_QUOTE_2",                          "你要是遭到了困难，或是受了委屈，有了急需要——那就去找穷人帮忙吧。只有他们才肯帮忙——只有他们。[NEWLINE]——约翰·恩斯特·斯坦贝克《愤怒的葡萄》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_PALEOBIOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                    "在无数世纪中经历了巨大变化的大自然本身就是一个最伟大、最微妙的化学现象，它能产生我们无法完成的事。[NEWLINE]——亚瑟·柯南·道尔《失落的世界》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_PALEOBIOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                    "我把地质记录视为一部保存不全的世界史，用不断变化的方言书写而成。[NEWLINE]——查尔斯·达尔文《物种起源》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_ANTHROPOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_1",                                    "政治上的民主、社会中的博爱、权利的平等和普及的教育，将揭开社会的下一个更高的阶段，经验、理智和知识正在不断向这个阶段努力。这将是古代氏族的自由、平等和博爱的复活，但却是在更高级形式上的复活。[NEWLINE]——路易斯·摩尔根《古代社会》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_ANTHROPOLOGY_HD_QUOTE_2",                                    "民族志田野工作首要而基本的理想便是，清楚而明了地勾画出所研究社会的结构，把所有文化现象中的定律、规则从不相干的事物中梳理出来。[NEWLINE]——勃洛尼斯拉夫·马林诺夫斯基《西太平洋上的航海者》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_URBAN_DESIGN_HD_QUOTE_1",                                    "所有视觉艺术活动的终极目标都是建造！[NEWLINE]——瓦尔特·格罗皮乌斯《包豪斯宣言》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_URBAN_DESIGN_HD_QUOTE_2",                                    "城市只有在所有人创造时，才能为所有人提供一切。[NEWLINE]——简·雅各布斯《美国大城市的死与生》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_LEAGUE_OF_NATIONS_HD_QUOTE_1",                               "任何战争或战争威胁，无论其是否立即影响本联盟任何会员国，兹宣告均为整个国际社会所应关切之事。国际联盟将采取任何经视为明智而有效之行动，以维护各国之和平。[NEWLINE]——《国际联盟盟约》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_LEAGUE_OF_NATIONS_HD_QUOTE_2",                               "威尔逊这位书生，天天在那里对那些强盗说“正义”、“人道”的话，组织“国际联盟”哪，希望“永久平和”哪，这真是对牛弹琴。只落得那些强盗们对他瞪眼，他自己也是对他们呕气，希望他的人灰心。[NEWLINE]——李大钊《秘密外交与强盗世界》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_FINANCE_HD_QUOTE_1",                                         "昨天各报纸上大书特书中央军胜利，交易所早市一声开拍，各项债券就涨上二三元，市场中密密层层的人头攒挤，呼喊的声音就像前线冲锋，什么话也听不清，只看见场上伸出来的手掌都是向上的。[NEWLINE]——茅盾《子夜》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_FINANCE_HD_QUOTE_2",                                         "金融世界是个谜一样的世界，尽管事实难以置信，但价值蒸发总是先于企业清盘。[NEWLINE]——约瑟夫·康拉德《胜利：一个岛屿的传说》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_HIGHER_EDUCATION_HD_QUOTE_1",                                "若我们不能用先知和他的同伴，以及那些宗教学习和指导的学者来慰己，那眼泪便会流连不止，因那教师的消逝和那学问之火已然为薪。[NEWLINE]——西迪·叶海亚·塔达利斯，转引自阿卜杜勒拉赫曼·萨迪《苏丹史集》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_HIGHER_EDUCATION_HD_QUOTE_2",                                "自由之风永远吹拂。[NEWLINE]——斯坦福大学校训"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_NEOCOLONIALISM_HD_QUOTE_1",                                  "所谓国际分工就是指一些国家专门赢利，而另外一些国家专门遭受损失。[NEWLINE]——爱德华多·加来亚诺《拉丁美洲被切开的血管》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_NEOCOLONIALISM_HD_QUOTE_2",                                  "如果一个国家在法律上独立而事实上依附，即可被称为新殖民主义或附庸国。其政治权力掌握在前殖民地的保守势力手中，经济权力则由国际金融资本控制。[NEWLINE]—— 夸梅·恩克鲁玛《虚假的独立》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_MODERNISM_HD_QUOTE_1",                                       "万物分崩离析，[NEWLINE]中心难再维系。[NEWLINE]——叶芝《第二次降临》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_MODERNISM_HD_QUOTE_2",                                       "戏剧与瘟疫都具有有益的作用，因为它促使人看见真实的自我，它撕下面具，揭露谎言、懦弱、卑鄙、伪善，它打破危及敏锐感觉的、令人窒息的物质惰性。[NEWLINE]——安托南·阿尔托《戏剧与瘟疫》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_INTERNATIONALISM_HD_QUOTE_1",                                "极愿一切非洲国家从此统一起来，使它们各国人民的繁荣与福利得以保证，决心通过建立与加强共同机构的方法以增强我们各国之间的联系，一致同意本宪章。[NEWLINE]——《非洲统一组织宪章》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_INTERNATIONALISM_HD_QUOTE_2",                                "西方侵略者几百年来只要在东方一个海岸上架起几尊大炮就可霸占一个国家的时代是一去不复返了，今天的任何帝国主义的侵略都是可以依靠人民的力量击败的。[NEWLINE]——彭德怀《关于中国人民志愿军抗美援朝工作的报告》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_MODERN_MATIONAL_DEFENSE_HD_QUOTE_1",                         "我相信这样说表达了国会和人民的意志：我断言，我们不仅将尽全力保卫我们自己，而且将确保永远不再受到这种背信弃义行为的危害。[NEWLINE]——富兰克林·罗斯福《关于对日本宣战对国会的演讲》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_MODERN_MATIONAL_DEFENSE_HD_QUOTE_2",                         "他于1918年10月阵亡。那天，整个前线寂静无声。军队指挥部战报上的记录仅有一句：西线无战事。[NEWLINE]——埃里希·玛利亚·雷马克《西线无战事》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_MACRO_ECONOMICS_HD_QUOTE_1",                                 "经济学家和政治哲学家们的思想，不论它们在对的时候还是在错的时候，都比一般所设想的要更有力量。[NEWLINE]——梅纳德·凯恩斯《就业、货币与利息通论》"),
  ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_CIVIC_MACRO_ECONOMICS_HD_QUOTE_2",                                 "同社会主义比较，资本主义是祸害。但同中世纪制度、同小生产、同小生产者涣散性引起的官僚主义比较，资本主义则是幸福。[NEWLINE]——弗拉基米尔·列宁《论粮食税、贸易自由、租让制》");